                            <comment id="11971" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 13 Jan 2005 07:34:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, that was more or less a deliberate design decision. That&apos;s also the reason why the tags reside in the &quot;web.servlet.tags&quot; package instead of a &quot;web.tags&quot; package (to indicate their dependency on DispatcherServlet, like the other subpackages of &quot;web.servlet&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tags usually need context information like MessageSource and Locale, which they currently get from DispatcherServlet. We could open this up a bit to also work with the root WebApplicationContext and HttpServletRequest.getLocale(), for example.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11973" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 13 Jan 2005 18:30:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Keith,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The RequestContext and all Spring JSP Tags work outside a DispatcherServlet too now, falling back to the root WebApplicationContext as MessageSource. For the locale, a JSTL locale attribute is detected (&quot;javax.servlet.jsp.jstl.fmt.locale&quot;), else the accept-header locale is used (request.getLocale).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11975" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 13 Jan 2005 18:42:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve also added an &quot;exposeRequestAttributes(ServletRequest request, Map attributes)&quot; method to WebUtils, for easy exposure of a model Map outside a DispatcherServlet. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  BindException ex = new BindException(new TestBean(), &quot;tb&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
  WebUtils.exposeRequestAttributes(request, ex.getModel());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A subsequent rendering of a JSP with Spring bind tags will work nicely even outside a DispatcherServlet then, detecting the given bean and Errors instance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exposing a plain bean will work too, because BindStatus does not depend on an existing Errors instance anymore. Of course, no errors and no custom property rendering will be available in such a case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
